                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>My dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Not wishing to allow you again to accuse me<lb/>\n                                        of neglecting to send you any thing of interest that takes\n                                        place<lb/> in our small congregation, I hasten to make you\n                                        acquainted with the<lb/> fact that \"The annual Examination\n                                        of the Sunday School took place on<lb/>\n                                        <date>Sunday 23 March</date>, it was attended by our\n                                                  <add>?</add> president and all the<lb/> members of\n                                        the congregation. There were near thirty children<lb/>\n                                        present and all acquitted themselves well. The elder boys\n                                        under<lb/> the immediate tuition of our able Hazan the\n                                                  <persName>Revd Mr DeSola</persName><lb/>\n                                        translated portions of the mishna, Bible prayers &amp;c\n                                        &amp;c<lb/> and were made to <sic>analyse</sic> several\n                                        difficult sentences<lb/> which they did with great facility,\n                                        affording evidence of <del>his</del><lb/> the great progress\n                                        they have made since last year. The<lb/> younger ones (boys\n                                        &amp; girls) under the tuition of the Lady<lb/> teachers\n                                        were carefully examined in \"Scripture Questions\"<lb/> \"Pykes\n                                        Chatechism\" \"The Creed\" \"Ten Commandments\" and also<lb/>\n                                        replied with great readiness and evinced great<lb/>\n                                        imprisonment, thus showing how faithfully their\n                                        teachers<lb/> perform this pleasing <add>?</add> they have\n                                        voluntarily assumed</p>\n                              <p>Before commencing the examinations, the whole together<lb/> sang\n                                                  <hi rend=\"underline\">In Relohenu</hi><add>?</add>\n                                        in very good voice and closed with<lb/> repeating <del>all\n                                                  together</del> the <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                                                  >She<add>?</add></hi>. <sic>Prises</sic> are\n                                        not<lb/> distributed that way owing to some mistake, but\n                                        since which<lb/> all the most deserving have received some\n                                        little token<lb/> as a reward for their exertions.\"</p>\n                              <p>I have nothing else of interest to offer you just now except</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3rn30t65/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
